ty.%20That%20year%2C%20they%20had%20their%20Eureka%20moment%2C%20he%20said.%20After%20learning%20New%20York%20state%20was%20softening%20restrictions%20on%20smaller%20craft%20distilleries%2C%20they%20decided%20they%20would%20start%20one%20themselves%20on%20Adams'%20family's%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20he%20said%20they%20did%20so%20knowing%20they'd%20be%20continuing%20the%20legacy%20of%20the%20site%2C%20which%20he%20said%20once%20held%20the%20largest%20bootlegging%20operation%20in%20Dutchess%20County%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fphotos-of-1920s-100-years-ago-2020%5C%22%3Eduring%20Prohibition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20period%20between%201920%20to%201933%20when%20the%20production%2C%20transport%2C%20and%20sale%20of%20alcohol%20in%20the%20US%20was%20outlawed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESchlein%20got%20to%20know%20the%20murky%20backstory%20of%20the%20land%20through%20Adams%2C%20whose%20grandfather%20worked%20as%20an%20errand%20boy%20when%20the%20site%20was%20used%20to%20make%20illegal%20moonshine%20in%20the%201930s.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225166%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20land%20could%20be%20where%20a%20legendary%20American%20mobster%20Dutch%20Shultz%20buried%20treasure.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c266ac101bd0001929d234%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222903%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20property%20was%20once%20home%20to%20an%20illegal%20bootlegging%20operation.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Houlihan%20Lawrence%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESchlein%2C%20who%20met%20Adams%20during%20college%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%2C%20said%20much%20of%20what%20he's%20come%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20origins%20of%20Harvest%20Homestead%20was%20through%20his%20friend's%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Adams'%20grandfather%2C%20Charles%20Adams%2C%20bought%20the%20property%20with%20his%20wife%2030%20years%20after%20he%20had%20worked%20as%20an%20errand%20boy%