g%20width%3D%5C%224743%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20bunkers%20were%20excavated%20and%20renovated.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c266cd101bd0001929d269%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223162%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThere%20are%20over%202%2C000-square-feet%20of%20bunkers%20below%20the%20modern%20building.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Houlihan%20Lawrence%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20couldn't%20destroy%202%2C000-square-feet%20of%20bunkers%2C%26quot%3B%20Schlein%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20bunkers%20and%20tunnels%2C%20they%20were%20made%20of%20concrete%2024%20inches%20thick%20with%20steel%20running%20through%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20renovation%20process%20began%2C%20he%20said%20he%20worked%20with%20archaeologists%20to%20ensure%20the%20tunnels%20and%20bunkers%20were%20not%20just%20structurally%20sound%20enough%20to%20welcome%20guests%20for%20tours%20below%20what%20would%20eventually%20become%20the%20modern%20distillery%2C%20but%20so%20that%20history%20was%20preserved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20property%20is%20now%20eligible%20for%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Historic%20Places%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.houlihanlawrence.com%2Fproperty%2F524828342%2F98-ryan-road-pine-plains-ny-12567%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20listing.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20the%20illegal%20distillery%20was%20operated%20by%20a%20legendary%20American%20gangster%2C%20who%20is%20rumored%20to%20have%20left%20treasure%20buried%20somewhere%20on%20the%20land%2C%20Schlein%20said.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224129%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mugshot%20of%20the%20American%20gangster%20Arthur%20'Dutch%20Schultz'%20Flegenheimer%20taken%20in%201935.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c27f3b048ff200190b88b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222215%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20mugshot%20of%20the%20American%20gangster%20Arthur%20%26quot%3BDutch%20Schultz%26quot%3B%20Flegenheimer%20taken%20in%201935.%3Cp%3EHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20listing%2C%20Arthur%20%26quot%3BDutch%20Schultz%26quot%3B%20Flegenheimer%2C%20was%20the%20No.%201%20suspect%20behind%20the%20illegal%20moonshine%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchultz%20rose%20to%20notoriety%20by%20creating%20his%20own%20enterprise%20and%20overseeing%20a%20gang%20that%20sold%20illegal%20batches%20of%20alcohol%20throughout%20New%20York%20City%20during%20Prohibition%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fbi.gov%2Fhistory%2Fartifacts%2Fbrick-from-the-palace-chop-house-dutch-schultz-murder-case%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20FBI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Not%20surprisingly%2C%20he%20had%20several%20run-ins%20with%20the%20law%20as%20well%20as%20enemy%20mobsters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Schultz's%20empire%20came%20crumbling%20down%20one%20night%20in%20October%201935%20when%20he%20and%20four%20of%20his%20associates%20were%20shot%20at%20a%20restaurant%20in%20New%20Jersey.%20He%20died%20the%20following%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20rumors%20continue%20to%20this%20day%20that%20before%20he%20was%20killed%2C%20Schultz%20stashed%20treasure%20somewhere%20in%20Upstate%20New%20York%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesunion.com%2Fhudsonvalley%2Fnews%2Farticle%2Fmodern-hunt-for-dutch-schultz-treasure-catskills-16317319.php%3FIPID%3DTimes-Union-HP-CP-Spotlight%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20local%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Schlein%20told%20Insider%20that%20some%20even%20suspect%20it's%20hidden%20on%20the%20land%20Harvest%20Homestead%20sits%20on%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20stories%20that%20gets%20bandied%20about%20is%20that%20Dutch%20Schultz%2C%20before%20he%20died%2C%20reportedly%20b