ww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Feu-trade-deal-risk-affordability-generic-medicine-global-south%2F%5C%22%3Ecautioned%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20potential%20fallouts%20of%20EU%20policy%20that%20could%20threaten%20the%20affordability%20of%20generic%20medicines%20these%20countries%20export%20to%20the%20Global%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7284150%2F%23ref-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingle%20largest%3C%2Fa%3E%20supplier%20of%20pharmaceutical%20products%20to%20Africa%20in%202018%2C%20and%20accounted%20for%20a%20fifth%20of%20the%20continent%E2%80%99s%20pharmaceutical%20imports%2C%20Ki-Moon%20and%20Winnie%20Byanyima%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20UNAIDS%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Feu-trade-deal-risk-affordability-generic-medicine-global-south%2F%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Cem%3EPolitico%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUNAIDS%20is%20the%20United%20Nations%E2%80%99%20programme%20on%20HIV%2FAIDS%20that%20works%20with%2011%20UN%20organisations%20to%20achieve%20universal%20access%20to%20HIV%20prevention%2C%20treatment%2C%20care%20and%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lessons%20learned%20from%20the%20HIV%20and%20AIDS%20pandemic%20highlight%20the%20significance%20of%20affordable%20generic%20medicines.%20India%E2%80%99s%20contribution%20of%20reasonably%20priced%20generic%20drugs%20helped%20lower%20treatment%20costs%20for%20AIDS%20from%20over%20%2410%2C000%20to%20less%20than%20%24100%20annually%20which%20saved%20countless%20lives.%20This%20was%20possible%20as%20the%20medicines%20were%20developed%20before%20India%20implemented%20the%201995%20World%20Trade%20Organization%20(WTO)%20agreement%20on%20Trade-Related%20Aspects%20of%20Intellectual%20Property%20Rights%20(TRIPS)%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20vital%20role%20in%20supplying%20affordable%20medical%20products%20was%20also%20evident%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20However%2C%20the%20EU%20and%20other%20developed%20nations%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Feu-trade-deal-risk-affordability-generic-medicine-global-south%2F%5C%22%3Efacing%20relentless%20lobbying%20from%20the%20pharmaceutical%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20opposed%20India%20and%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20to%20temporarily%20waive%20some%20TRIPS%20obligations%20for%20COVID-19%20medical%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20TRIPS%20agreement%20aimed%20to%20foster%20innovation%20and%20social%20benefits%2C%20critics%20argue%20that%20it%20has%20tipped%20the%20scales%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20pharmaceutical%20industry%2C%20compromising%20access%20to%20affordable%20medications.%20The%20development%20of%20long-acting%20HIV%20prevention%20and%20treatment%20medicines%2C%20with%20the%20potential%20to%20advance%20the%20end%20of%20AIDS%2C%20relies%20on%20wide%20availability%20at%20low%20prices%20through%20large-scale%20generic%20production%2C%20the%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Feu-trade-deal-risk-affordability-generic-medicine-global-south%2F%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20negotiations%20with%20Indonesia%2C%20the%20EU%20has%20proposed%20an%20extensive%20intellectual%20property%20enforcement%20regime%20that%20could%20negatively%20impact%20access%20to%20medicines.%20Furthermore%2C%20it%20wants%20to%20extend%20pharmaceutical%20patent%20monopolies%20and%20expand%20exclusive%20data%20rights%2C%20which%20could%20cause%20delays%20in%20the%20availability%20of%20cost-effective%20generic%20versions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPast%20experiences%20with%20similar%20proposals%2C%20termed%20TRIPS-plus%20measures%2C%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20their%20implications%20on%20access%20to%20medicines.%20In%20countries%20like%20Jordan%20and%20Guatemala%2C%20the%20implementation%20of%20data%20exclusivity%20clauses%20in%20trade%20agreements%20resulted%20in%20delays%20in%20accessing%20more%20affordable%20generic%20alternatives%2C%20straining%20public%20health%20programs%20financially.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20U.N.%20Special%20Rapporteur%20on%20the%20Right%20to%20Health%20said%20that%20developed%20countries%20should%20not%20encourage%20developing%20nations%20to%20enter%20into%20trade%20agreements%20with%20TRIPS-plus%20measures%2C%20as%20they%20infringe%20upon%20the%20right%20to%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecognizing%20the%20importance%20of%20medicines%20as%20global%20public%20goods%2C%20the%20European%20Parliament%20has%20repeatedly%20called%20on%20the%20Commission%20to%20exclude%20TRIPS-plus%20requirements%20in%20trade%20negotiations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20negotiators%20note%20they%E2%80%99ve%20%E2%80%9Cfirmly%20communicated%E2%80%9D%20that%20data%20exclusivity%20and%20patent%20term%20extensions%20are%20%E2%80%9Credlines%E2%80%9D%20for%20them%20in%20these%20negotiations%20and%20that%20the%20EU%20should%20never%20have%20demanded%20such%20changes%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EPolitico%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Feu-trade-deal-risk-affordability-generic-medicine-global-south%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690627829000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F29143605%2F1024px-Ebola_Vaccine_Study_in_West_Africa_33833442616.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fban-ki-moon-flags-potential-impact-of-eu-trade-deals-on-indias-generic-medicine-exports%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20EU's%20proposals%20for%20stricter%20protection%20of%20intellectual%20property%20rights%20could%20hinder%20access%20to%20cost-effective%20medicines%20that%20India%20exports%20to%20the%20Global%20South.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fban-ki-moon-flags-po