te%20to%20clients%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%20since%20January%201987%2C%20the%20Dow%20Jones%20Industrial%20Average%20closed%20in%20the%20green%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-dow-jones-win-streak-no-recession-economy-2023-7%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Dow%2520Jones%2520Industrial%2520Average%2Cis%2520no%2520recession%2520in%2520sight.%5C%22%3E13%20straight%20sessions%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20snapping%20its%20winning%20streak%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStocks%20were%20up%2028%25%20at%20this%20point%20in%201987%2C%20Rosenberg%20noted.%20But%20they%20erased%20those%20gains%20over%20the%20next%20five%20months%2C%20in%20large%20part%20because%20the%20Dow%20tanked%2022%25%20on%20October%2019%20that%20year%20%E2%80%94%20a%20date%20now%20known%20as%20Black%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20giddiness%20was%20omnipresent%20as%20is%20the%20case%20today%20and%20the%20bears%20were%20laughed%20at%20%E2%80%A6%20but%20look%20at%20how%20the%20year%20ended%20%E2%80%A6%20FLAT!%26quot%3B%20the%20Rosenberg%20Research%20president%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20cautioned%20investors%20who%20expect%20stocks%20to%20soar%20because%20inflation%20has%20now%20slowed.%20The%20pace%20of%20price%20increases%20has%20plunged%20from%209.1%25%20to%203%25%20over%20the%20last%2012%20months%2C%20fueling%20hopes%20that%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20will%20halt%20its%20interest-rate%20hikes%20and%20soon%20reverse%20them%2C%20enabling%20the%20US%20economy%20to%20avoid%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20chief%20North%20American%20economist%20at%20Merrill%20Lynch%20emphasized%20that%20inflation%20typically%20cools%20because%20demand%20has%20dropped%2C%20and%20that%20usually%20translates%20into%20slimmer%20corporate%20profits%20and%20pressure%20on%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20Rosenberg%20pointed%20out%20that%20inflation%20fell%20sharply%20during%20the%20dot-com%20era%2C%20the%20financial%20crisis%2C%20and%20the%20early-1980s%20downturn%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20tanked%2026%25%2C%2030%25%2C%20and%208%25%20during%20each%20of%20those%20periods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20he%20complained%20that%20some%20stocks%20are%20exorbitantly%20priced%20as%20a%20result%20of%20investors'%20fear%20of%20missing%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20say%20that%20either%20long-only%20investors%20don't%20own%20a%20calculator%20or%20can't%20do%20the%20math%20on%20relative%20valuations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20FOMO-based%20rallies%20look%20like%20%E2%80%94%20inversely%20correlated%20to%20rational%20thought.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20veteran%20economist%20also%20advised%20against%20ruling%20out%20an%20economic%20contraction%2C%20even%20though%20gross%20domestic%20product%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgdp-gross-domestic-product-us-q2-2023-economy-growth-2023-7%5C%22%3Eproven%20surprisingly%20resilient%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20very%20possible%20that%20the%20recession%20has%20started%20already%2C%20but%20nobody%20has%20noticed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20very%20quarters%20that%20the%20recessions%20of%201990%2C%202001%20and%202007%20began%2C%20the%20narrative%20was%20'soft%20landing'%20each%20and%20every%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg's%20doom-and-gloom%20predictions%20place%20him%20firmly%20in%20the%20minority.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fpaul-krugman-soft-landing-recession-inflation-cpi-report-fed-unemployment-2023-7%5C%22%3EMany%20other%20experts%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20issued%20brighter%20outlooks%3B%20they%20see%20asset%20prices%20rising%20and%20minimal%20risk%20of%20a%20recession%20as%20the%20Fed%20begins%20loosening%20its%20grip%20on%20the%20US%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%