A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20universe%2C%20man%20and%20animals%20are%20equally%20placed%2C%20but%20human%20rights%20approach%20to%20environmental%20protection%20in%20case%20of%20conflict%2C%20is%20often%20based%20on%20anthropocentricity.%20Man-animal%20conflict%20often%20results%20not%20because%20animals%20encroach%20human%20territories%20but%20vice%20versa%E2%80%A6This%20Court%20cannot%20blink%20at%20the%20reality%20that%20often%20at%20the%20State%20level%2C%20regional%2C%20parochial%2C%20anthropomorphic%2C%20and%20times%2C%20even%20narrow%20political%20considerations%20would%20prevail%20over%20the%20more%20significant%20national%20interests%20involved%20in%20conserving%20and%20protecting%20the%20tiger%20and%20the%20tiger%20habitat%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20division%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20Sonak%20and%20Deshpande%20observed%2C%20in%20what%20may%20be%20the%20most%20striking%20comment%20in%20recent%20times%20in%20the%20development%20versus%20conservation%20debate%20across%20the%20globe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20plea%20to%20convert%20the%20MHADEI%20wildlife%20sanctuary%20into%20a%20tiger%20reserve%20was%20moved%20by%20the%20Goa%20Foundation%2C%20a%20non-profit%20environment%20rights%20advocacy%20organisation.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flawbeat.in%2Fnews-updates%2Fbombay-high-court-orders-goa-government-declare-mhadei-wildlife-sanctuary-tiger%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3ELawbeat%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20union%20government%20and%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20since%202011%20had%20been%20making%20several%20requests%20to%20the%20Goa%20government%20to%20notify%20the%20Mhadei%20wildlife%20sanctuary%20and%20some%20contiguous%20forest%20areas%20as%20tiger%20reserve.%20But%20the%20Goa%20government%20remained%20opposed%20to%20it%2C%20citing%20conflicting%20interests%20between%20forest%20dwellers%20and%20advocates%20of%20conservation.%20However%2C%20conservation%20experts%20have%20alleged%20that%20the%20declaration%20of%20the%20wildlife%20sanctuary%20into%20a%20tiger%20reserve%20may%20restrict%20the%20Goa%20government%E2%80%99s%20aim%20to%20open%20up%20forest%20resources%20for%20commercial%20use.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20matter%20came%20to%20a%20head%20when%20in%20January%202020%20a%20tigress%20and%20three%20cubs%20died%20due%20to%20some%20poisoning%20in%20the%20sanctuary.%20The%20Goa%20Foundation%2C%20citing%20government%20inaction%2C%20moved%20the%20high%20court%20thereafter.%20The%20matter%20was%20being%20heard%20at%20the%20Goa%20Bench%20of%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20since%20then.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20directing%20the%20Goa%20government%20to%20declare%20the%20sanctuary%20as%20a%20tiger%20reserve%2C%20the%20bench%20observed%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20tiger%20is%20a%20unique%20animal%20which%20plays%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20the%20health%20and%20diversity%20of%20an%20ecosystem.%20It%20is%20a%20top%20predator%20at%20the%20apex%20of%20the%20food%20chain.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20tigers%20in%20the%20forest%20is%20an%20indicator%20of%20the%20well-being%20of%20the%20ecosystem.%20Protection%20of%20tigers%20in%20forests%20protects%20the%20habitats%20of%20several%20other%20species.%20Indirect%20benefits%20of%20preserving%20a%20tiger%20include%20several%20ecosystem%20services%20like%20protection%20of%20rivers%20and%20other%20water%20sources%2C%20prevention%20of%20soil%20erosion%20and%20improvement%20of%20ecological%20services%20like%20pollination%2C%20water%20table%20retention%2C%20etc.%20Conversely%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20this%20top%20predator%20indicates%20that%20its%20ecosystem%20is%20not%20sufficiently%20protected.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Goa%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20counsel%20cited%20many%20references%20in%20which%20the%20Goa%20government%20refused%20to%20respond%20to%20repeated%20requests%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%2C%20alleging%20inaction%20and%20failure%20to%20stick%20to%20its%20statutory%20duty%20on%20its%20part.%20The%20Goa%20government%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20claimed%20that%20it%20had%20at%20no%20point%20refused%20to%20send%20a%20proposal%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20about%20converting%20the%20sanctuary%20into%20a%20tiger%20reserve%20or%20notify%20is%20as%20one%20but%20added%20that%20the%20time%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20right%20for%20sanctuary%20to%20be%20declared%20as%20a%20tiger%20reserve%20as%20some%20issues%20regarding%20forest%20dwellers%20needed%20to%20be%20settled%20first.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20Goa%20government%20cited%20the%20recommendations%20of%20Goa%E2%80%99s%20state%20board%20for%20wildlife%20which%20had%20recently%20rejected%20the%20idea%20of%20setting%20up%20a%20tiger%20reserve%20in%20the%20MHADEI%20wildlife%20sanctuary%2C%20arguing%20that%20such%20a%20decision%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cpremature%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20feasible%E2%80%9D.%20Even%20the%20chief%20minister%20Pramod%20Sawant%20said%20that%20the%20Wildlife%20Act%20and%20the%20NTCA%E2%80%99s%20guidelines%20were%20not%20fit%20to%20be%20implemented%20in%20a%20small%20state%20like%20Goa.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20repeated%20delays%20in%20responding%20to%20central%20notices%20and%20unclear%20positions%20led%20the%20high%20court%20to%20rule%20against%20the%20Goa%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EState%E2%80%99s%20forest%20minister%20Vishwajit%20Rane%20said%20that%20the%20state%20government%20will%20move%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20vacate%20the%20order.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20examining%20the%20HC%20order%2C%20we%20shall%20explore%20all%20options%20before%20approaching%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20have%20this%20order%20vacated.%20We%20respect%20the%20decision%20taken%20by%20the%20HC%2C%20but%20as%20a%20State%20Government%2C%20we%2