around%20accelerating%20climate%20action%2C%20land%20degradation%20and%20how%20to%20reduce%20and%20prevent%20it%2C%20restoring%20ecosystems%20and%20halting%20biodiversity%20loss%2C%20promoting%20resource%20efficiency%20and%20a%20circular%20economy%2C%20addressing%20pollution%20and%20promoting%20a%20blue%20or%20ocean-based%20economy.%20Topics%20like%20ecological%20restoration%2C%20marine%20spatial%20planning%2C%20and%20circular%20economy%20were%20addressed%20in%20detail%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20G20%20discussions%2C%20reported%20PTI.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20recall%20and%20reaffirm%20the%20commitment%20made%20by%20developed%20countries%20to%20the%20goal%20of%20mobilising%20jointly%20USD%20100%20billion%20climate%20finance%20per%20year%20by%202020%2C%20and%20annually%20through%202025%2C%20to%20address%20the%20needs%20of%20developing%20countries%2C%20in%20the%20context%20of%20meaningful%20mitigation%20action%20and%20transparency%20in%20implementation.%20Developed%20country-contributors%20expect%20this%20goal%20to%20be%20met%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%202023%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20document%20read.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20meeting%20also%20discussed%20sustainable%20water%20resource%20management%2C%20and%20members%20called%20for%20the%20appointment%20of%20a%20UN%20Special%20Envoy%20on%20Water%2C%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D%2C%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccontribute%20to%20positive%20actions%20aimed%20at%20meeting%20global%20water%20challenges%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELack%20of%20consensus%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20there%20was%20a%20lack%20of%20consensus%20on%20several%20aspects%2C%20which%20the%20outcome%20document%20encapsulated%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9CChair%E2%80%99s%20Summary%E2%80%9D%2C%20versus%20a%20joint%20communique%20that%20signifies%20consensus%20amongst%20the%20G20%20countries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERegarding%20the%20discussion%20on%20mitigation%20mechanisms%2C%20some%20G20%20members%20%E2%80%9Cemphasised%E2%80%9D%20the%20%E2%80%9Cneed%20for%20a%20global%20peaking%20of%20emissions%20no%20later%20than%202025%2C%20and%20reduction%20in%20emissions%20by%2060%25%20by%202035%20over%202019%20levels%E2%80%9D.%20The%20talks%20also%20covered%20historical%2C%20current%20and%20projected%20carbon%20emissions%2C%20climate%20finance%20and%20attaining%20net%20zero.%20Some%20G20%20members%20stated%20the%20need%20for%20developed%20countries%20to%20reach%20net%20zero%20by%202040.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Flack-of-unanimity-on-climate-targets-among-g20-delegates%5C%22%3ELack%20of%20Unanimity%20on%20Climate%20Targets%20Among%20G20%20Delegates%20Worries%20COP%20Organisers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Summary%20also%20mentions%20discussions%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20clean%20energy%20transitions%2C%20including%20accelerating%20the%20scaling%20up%20of%20renewable%20energy%2C%20tripling%20renewable%20capacity%2C%20and%20phasing%20down%20fossil%20fuels.%20There%20%E2%80%9Cexist%20divergent%20views%E2%80%9D%20among%20members%20on%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20Working%20Group%20to%20discuss%20energy%20issues%20in%20light%20of%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20separate%20Energy%20Transition%20Working%20Group%2C%20and%20on%20issues%20surrounding%20energy%20transitions%20%E2%80%9Cand%20how%20to%20reflect%20them%20in%20this%20document%E2%80%9D%2C%20per%20the%20Summary.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%E2%80%9Ctext%20indicated%20that%20negotiations%20were%20mired%20in%20differences%2C%20with%20countries%20failing%20to%20rise%20beyond%20politics%E2%80%9D%2C%20commented%20Madhura%20Joshi%2C%20Senior%20Associate%2C%20Fossil%20Fuel%20Transition%20Team%2C%20E3G.%20The%20outcomes%2C%20especially%20on%20energy%2C%20leave%20a%20lot%20to%20be%20desired%2C%20she%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20has%20an%20opportunity%20to%20drive%20the%20new%20engine%20of%20the%20global%20economy%20by%20leading%20the%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20summit%20in%20September%20to%20course%20correct%20climate%20action%20and%20agreeing%20to%20%E2%80%93%20tripling%20renewables%20by%202030%20to%20over%2011%2C000GW%2C%20doubling%20the%20rate%20of%20energy%20efficiency%2C%20and%20phasing%20out%20fossil%20fuels.%20This%20is%20what%20the%20science%20tells%20us%20is%20difficult%20but%20feasible%20and%20critical%20for%20keeping%201.5%20alive.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20document%20very%20rightly%20acknowledges%20that%20the%20efforts%20are%20insufficient%20to%20limit%20the%20global%20temperatures%20to%201.5%20degree%20Celsius%2C%20said%20Vibhuti%20Garg%2C%20Director%2C%20South%20Asia%2C%20Institute%20for%20Energy%20Economics%20and%20Financial%20Analysis%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20But%20given%20the%20increasing%20extreme%20weather%20events%20worldwide%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20are%20sitting%20on%20a%20ticking%20bomb%E2%80%9D%2C%20she%20commented.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20transition%20should%20be%20fair%2C%20just%20and%20equitable%2C%20we%20need%20increased%20commitments%20and%20more%20importantly%20increased%20implementation%20of%20energy%20transition%20in%20different%20sectors%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20will%20imply%20tripling%20of%20renewable%20energy%20targets%20and%20doubling%20of%20energy%20efficiency%20and%20we%20need%20enhanced%20commitment%20from%20countries%20on%20this%20front.%20Also%2C%20access%20to%20climate%20finance%20especially%20by%20the%20low%20income%20countries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EChennai%20High-Level%20Principles%20adopted%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20G20%20members%20adopted%20the%20%E2%80%98Chennai%20High-Level%20Principles%20for%20a%20Sustainable%20and%20Resilient%20Blue%2F%20Ocean-based%20Economy%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20can%20be%20implemented%20on%20a%20voluntary%20basis%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbased%20on%20national%20circumstances%20and%20priorities%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20document%E2%80%99s%20nine%20principles%20are%20prioritizing%20ocean%20health%20(by%20addressing%20marine%20pollution%2C%20halting%20and%20reversing%20biodiversity%20loss%20and%20conserving%20coastal%20and%20marine%20ecosystems)%3B%20acknowledging%20and%20addressing%20the%20links%20between%20ocean%20and%20climate%3B%20promote%20social%20or%20inter-generational%20equity%20and%20gender%20equality%20in%20ocean-based%20economy%20strategies%3B%20promote%20the%20use%20of%20Marine%20Spatial%20Planning%2C%20which%20will%20bring%20multiple%20stakeholders%20across%20all%20linked%20fields%20to%20make%20informed%20and%20coordinated%20decisions%20on%20the%20sustainable%20use%20of%20marine%20resources%3B%20leverage%20science%2C%20technology%20and%20innovation%20in%20creating%20a%20sustainable%20ocean-based%20economy%3B%20recognize%2C%20protect%20and%20utilize%20indigenous%20and%20traditional%20knowledge%3B%20establish%20and%20implement%20ocean-based%20economy%20monitoring%20and%20evaluation%20mechanisms%3B%20strengthen%20international%20cooperation%20to%20deal%20with%20shared%20maritime%20challenges%20and%20enhance%20ocean%20finance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98India%20in%20forefront%E2%80%99%20of%20biodiversity%20conservation%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20has%20consistently%20been%20at%20the%20forefront%20in%20taking%20action%20on%20biodiversity%20conservation%2C%20protection%2C%20restoration%2C%20and%20enrichment%2C%20and%20has%20set%20the%20bar%20even%20higher%20through%20its%20updated%20targets%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20said%20on%20Friday%2C%20while%20addressing%20the%20G20%20Environment%20and%20Climate%20Sustainability%20Ministerial%20Meeting%20via%20video%20conferencing%2C%20%3C%2F