p%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20%E2%80%9Cproblems%E2%80%9D%20with%20Nirva%E2%80%99s%20radio%20collar%2C%20but%20monitoring%20teams%20are%20observing%20the%20animal%20closely%2C%20one%20of%20the%20sources%20said.%20The%20teams%20sighted%20her%20directly%20and%20were%20also%20able%20to%20see%20her%20pugmarks%20and%20other%20indirect%20signs%20%E2%80%93%20so%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20%E2%80%9Cworry%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20animal%2C%20the%20source%20added.%20Plans%20are%20still%20on%20to%20capture%20the%20two%20animals%2C%20the%20source%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690554927000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F01124706%2FFr_KjcBXoAEm2rW.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fauthorities-yet-to-capture-last-two-free-ranging-cheetahs-in-kuno-national-park%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Officials%20have%20been%20darting%20all%20free-ranging%20cheetahs%20that%20were%20released%20in%20Kuno%20National%20Park%20as%20part%20of%20Project%20Cheetah%2C%20and%20bringing%20them%20back%20to%20enclosures%20in%20the%20Park%20to%20conduct%20health%20checks%20on%20the%20animals%20since%20mid%20July.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fauthorities-yet-to-capture-last-two-free-ranging-cheetahs-in-kuno-national-park%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22During%20Japan%20FM%E2%80%99s%20Visit%2C%20Japanese%20Firms%20Lobby%20for%20a%20Better%20Business%20Environment%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28191251%2Fimage-1179.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Japanese%20companies%20told%20the%20visiting%20foreign%20minister%2C%20Yoshimasa%20Hayashi%2C%20that%20they%20want%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20predictable%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ctransparent%E2%80%9D%20business%20environment%20in%20India%2C%20even%20as%20Tokyo%20said%20that%20it%20was%20up%20to%20India%20as%20the%20G20%20president%20to%20reach%20a%20consensus%20on%20language%20over%20Ukraine%20for%20a%20joint%20communique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Japanese%20foreign%20minister%20arrived%20in%20India%20on%20July%2028%2C%20Friday%20and%20chaired%20a%20Strategic%20Dialogue%20with%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar.%20On%20Friday%20morning%2C%20the%20two%20ministers%20took%20part%20in%20a%20public%20interaction%20at%20the%20India-Japan%20Forum.%20It%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20lunch%20meeting%20with%20representatives%20of%20Japanese%20companies%20and%20the%20Japan%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20and%20Industry%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20briefing%20for%20the%20Indian%20press%2C%20Japanese%20foreign%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20deputy%20press%20secretary%2C%20Yukiko%20Okano%2C%20said%20the%20%E2%80%9Cview%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20Japanese%20firms%20in%20India%20was%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthey%20would%20like%20to%20see%20a%20more%20predictable%2C%20stable%20and%20transparent%20business%20environment%E2%80%9D%2C%20especially%20related%20to%20regulatory%20and%20tax%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20while%20this%20was%20not%20discussed%20on%20Friday%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20have%20also%20heard%20that%20infrastructure%20challenges%20were%20raised%20in%20the%20past%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Japanese%20spokesperson%20noted%20that%20the%20business%20chambers%20had%20raised%20these%20issues%20with%20Indian%20authorities%20from%20time%20to%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20Japanese%20foreign%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20press%20release%20on%20the%20Strategic%20Dialogue%20had%20said%20that%20minister%20Hayashi%20had%20%E2%80%9Crequested%20cooperation%20to%20improve%20the%20investment%20environment%20and%20for%20the%20early%20establishment%20of%20a%20Joint%20Crediting%20Mechanism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20Japanese%20figures%2C%20Japan%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20third%20largest%20trading%20partner%20and%20fifth%20largest%20investor%20in%202021.%20There%20are%20around%201%2C439%20Japanese%20firms%20having%20presence%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20Japanese%20prime%20minister%20Fumio%20Kishida%E2%80%99s%20visit%20last%20year%2C%20a%20target%20of%20public%20and%20private%20investment%20of%20five%20trillion%20yen%20in%20India%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%20till%202027%20was%20established.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOkano%20said%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Csteady%E2%80%9D%20progress%20in%20meeting%20the%20target%2C%20but%20added%20that%20both%20sides%20were%20not%20releasing%20yearly%20figures%20on%20that%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsouth-korean-firms-havent-received-the-promised-incentives-as-part-of-pli-scheme-says-top-official%5C%22%3ECentre%20Accused%20of%20%E2%80%98Unfairly%E2%80%99%20Withholding%20Production%20Incentives%20to%20South%20Korean%20Firms%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20discussions%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%20on%20which%20India%20and%20Japan%20have%20varying%20positions%2C%20the%20Japanese%20diplomat%20said%20that%20both%20countries%20share%20%E2%80%9Cfundamental%20principles%E2%80%9D%20that%20%E2%80%9Cterritorial%20integrity%20and%20sovereignty%20should%20be%20protected%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20use%20of%20force%20to%20change%20status%20quo%20%E2%80%9Cis%20not%20permissible%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20reminded%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20good%20meeting%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20Ukrainian%20president%20Volodymyr%20Zelensky%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20G7%20summit%20hosted%20by%20Japan%20in%20Hiroshima.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20Japan%20wants%20Zelensky%20to%20participate%20at%20the%20G20%20summit%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20okay%20either%20way%20on%20whether%20India%20invites%20Zelensky.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20the%20language%20of%20the%20joint%20communique%20is%20still%20under%20discussion%20between%20the%20G20%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENoting%20that%20the%20G7%20will%20not%20dilute%20their%20position%20on%20Ukraine%20irrespective%20of%20the%20forum%2C%20the%20Japanese%20deputy%20press%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20joint%20communique%2C%20%5Bit%20is%5D%20up%20to%20the%20president%20on%20how%20to%20reach%20a%20consensus.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-ukraine-russia-criticise%5C%22%3EWhy%20Is%20India%20Unable%20to%20Criticise%20the%20Country%20That%20Has%20Invaded%20Ukraine%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20speaking%20at%20the%20India-Japan%20forum%2C%20Hayashi%20said%20that%20at%20a%20time%20when%20there%20are%20many%20pressing%20challenges%2C%20including%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20aggression%20against%20Ukraine%2C%20Japan%20and%20India%20%E2%80%9Cfully%20share%20the%20necessity%20to%20lead%20the%20world%20to%20cooperation%2C%20rather%20than%20to%20division%20and%20confrontation%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20free%20and%20open%20international%20order%20based%20on%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20is%20key%20to%20realising%20such%20a%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20India%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9Cindispensable%E2%80%9D%20partner%20in%20achieving%20a%20free%20and%20open%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20Hayashi%20said%20%E2%80%9Cfree%E2%80%9D%20means%20each%20country%20is%20free%20to%20make%20decisions%20based%20on%20its%20own%20sovereignty%20and%20%E2%80%9Copen%E2%80%9D%20means%20respect%20for%20principles%2C%20including%20inclusiveness%2C%20openness%20and%20diversity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20vital%20that%20we%20refrain%20from%20imposing%20values%20or%20excluding%20certain%20countries.%20This%20concept%20is%20especially%20crucial%20for%20smaller%20countries.%20In%20coordination%20with%20India%2C%20Japan%20intends%20to%20materialise%20such%20a%20concept%20through%20realising%20a%20%E2%80%98Free%20and%20Open%20Indo-Pacific%E2%80%99%20or%20FOIP%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Japanese%20prime%20minister%20will%20be%20back%20in%20India%20for%20the%20second%20consecutive%20year%20to%20attend%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690552839000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28191251%2Fimage-1179.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fduring-japan-fms-visit-japanese-firms-lobby-for-a-better-business-environment-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tokyo%20also%20said%20that%20it%20was%20up%20to%20India%20as%20the%20G20%20president%20to%20reach%20a%20consensus%20on%20language%20over%20Ukraine%20for%20a%20joint%20communique.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fduring-japan-fms-visit-japanese-firms-lobby-for-a-better-business-environment-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Key%20US%20inflation%20gauge%20cools%20further%20as%20rate%20hikes%20bite%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690552709000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102209046%2Cimgsize-1407545.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fkey-us-inflation-gauge-cools-further-as-rate-hikes-bite%2Farticleshow%2F102208855.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102208855.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EA%20key%20indicator%20of%20US%20inflation%20cooled%20in%20June%20to%20the%20lowest%20annual%20rate%20in%20over%20two%20years%2C%20although%20this%20remains%20above%20the%20c